Task 1: Set up Nginx as a Redirector for Traffic Obfuscation
Subtask 1.1: Install and Configure Nginx
First, we'll install Nginx and set it up as a reverse proxy redirector.

Step 1: Update the system packages

sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
Step 2: Install Nginx

sudo apt install nginx -y
Step 3: Start and enable Nginx service

sudo systemctl start nginx
sudo systemctl enable nginx
Step 4: Verify Nginx installation

sudo systemctl status nginx
curl localhost
You should see the default Nginx welcome page HTML output.

Subtask 1.2: Create a Custom Nginx Configuration for Redirection
Step 1: Create a backup of the default configuration

sudo cp /etc/nginx/sites-available/default /etc/nginx/sites-available/default.backup
Step 2: Create a new configuration file for our redirector

sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/redirector
Step 3: Add the following configuration to the file

server {
    listen 80;
    listen 443 ssl;
    server_name redirector.local;
    
    # SSL Configuration (self-signed for lab purposes)
    ssl_certificate /etc/nginx/ssl/nginx.crt;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/nginx/ssl/nginx.key;
    ssl_protocols TLSv1.2 TLSv1.3;
    ssl_ciphers HIGH:!aNULL:!MD5;
    
    # Log configuration
    access_log /var/log/nginx/redirector_access.log;
    error_log /var/log/nginx/redirector_error.log;
    
    # Main redirection logic
    location / {
        # Check for specific User-Agent (simulating C2 traffic)
        if ($http_user_agent ~* "RedTeamAgent") {
            proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8080;
            proxy_set_header Host $host;
            proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
            proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
            break;
        }
        
        # Default redirect to legitimate site
        return 301 https://www.example.com;
    }
    
    # Health check endpoint
    location /health {
        access_log off;
        return 200 "OK\n";
        add_header Content-Type text/plain;
    }
}
Step 4: Create SSL directory and generate self-signed certificates

sudo mkdir -p /etc/nginx/ssl
sudo openssl req -x509 -nodes -days 365 -newkey rsa:2048 \
    -keyout /etc/nginx/ssl/nginx.key \
    -out /etc/nginx/ssl/nginx.crt \
    -subj "/C=US/ST=State/L=City/O=Organization/CN=redirector.local"
Step 5: Enable the new site configuration

sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/redirector /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
sudo rm /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default
Step 6: Test the configuration and restart Nginx

sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl restart nginx
Subtask 1.3: Set up a Mock C2 Server
